The best approach for your .NET 10 project is the **`System.IO.Abstractions`** NuGet package — it's battle-tested and provides a drop-in `IFileSystem` interface covering `File.*`, `Directory.*`, `Path.*`, etc.

### 1. Install the packages

```bash
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions
# In your test project:
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

### 2. Register in DI

```csharp
// In Program.cs or Startup.cs:
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

### 3. Inject `IFileSystem` into your classes

Looking at `Services/ReportGenerator.cs`, you'd refactor it like this:

```csharp
using System.IO.Abstractions;

public class ReportGenerator(IFileSystem fileSystem)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        var outputDir = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("REPORT_OUTPUT_DIR") ?? "/tmp/reports";

        if (!fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))
        {
            fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);
        }

        var reportPath = fileSystem.Path.Combine(outputDir, $"{reportName}_...");
        fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);

        return reportPath;
    }
}
```

### 4. Test with `MockFileSystem`

```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem();
mockFs.AddDirectory("/tmp/reports");

var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs);
var path = generator.GenerateReport("sales");

Assert.True(mockFs.File.Exists(path));
Assert.Contains("Report: sales", mockFs.File.ReadAllText(path));
```

### Bonus: your other statics

I also noticed `DateTime.UtcNow`, `Environment.*`, and `Console.WriteLine` in that file. Quick recommendations:

| Static | Recommended abstraction |
|---|---|
| `DateTime.UtcNow` | **`TimeProvider`** (built-in in .NET 8+) — inject `TimeProvider.System`, test with `FakeTimeProvider` |
| `Environment.*` | Custom **`IEnvironmentProvider`** wrapping only `GetEnvironmentVariable` and `MachineName` |
| `Console.WriteLine` | Use `ILogger<T>` instead, or a custom `IConsole` if you truly need console output |

Want me to refactor `ReportGenerator.cs` with all of these abstractions wired up?
